RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 76. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRIGORO allowed to settle in the early going, advanced two wide on the far turn, continued that steady bid into the stretch run, came within aim of FANTASTIC SECRET nearing the furlong marker, battled with the runner-up into deep stretch and kept to task in the final stages to prevail. COCOA CENTS broke alertly, ceded the early lead to FANTASTIC SECRET and stalked that rival through moderate fractions, lost ground to FANTASTIC SECRET on the far turn, re-rallied in the drive, split foes in mid-stretch, had a narrow lead in deep stretch but was outfinished in the final stages and was second best. FANTASTIC SECRET showed early speed and was sent to establish the early advantage, cleared the field into the first turn and set moderate fractions to the half-mile marker, drew to a clear lead approaching the quarter pole, came under pressure nearing mid-stretch, could not hold off the top two late and just held for third in the final strides. DANGEROUS ILLUSION raced just off of the early pace, settled along the backstretch run, raced two wide into the stretch, mounted a mild late bid in the final furlong and just missed for show. ALESHA forwardly placed in the early stages, lost position while saving ground along the backstretch run, maintained that rail trip to the quarter pole, angled out in the stretch run and offered a mild late rally. ROSE PRINCESS hopped at the start and was off a step slowly, rushed up along the first turn and chased the moderate pace to the half-mile marker, lost ground on the far turn and did not offer a late rally. NICOLE GRACE lacked early speed, settled through the backstretch run, lost contact nearing the quarter pole and could not muster a late response.

ENTRY.COMMENT: close early,lost position backstretch,angled out stretch,mild bid

ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start,chased pace,lost ground 1/4,no late rally

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SYNNIN AND WINNIN broke in good order and assumed command in the early stages, set moderate fractions to the turn, was confronted by WAKES AND WEDDINGS nearing the quarter pole, quickened in upper stretch to dispose of that rival and drew off under steady hand urging in the final stages. WAKES AND WEDDINGS was forwardly placed in the early going and stalked the moderate fractions while outside of SYNNIN AND WINNIN, advanced on the pacesetter nearing the quarter pole, could not keep pace with SYNNIN AND WINNIN when that one quickened in upper stretch but stayed on in the late stages and just held for the place. WHISPER AND WINK chased the moderate early fractions, was a bit hard to handle on the turn while three wide and trying to get out, could not keep pace with the winner in the stretch and was outfinished in the final strides for the place. MOVIETIME was unprepared at the start then ducked in leaving the gate and was off slowly, rushed up heading into the turn, chased from the inside to the top of the lane and tired in the stretch.

TORPEDO AWAY tracked the fast early pace, advanced two wide on the turn, swung four wide into the stretch drive, rallied inside of the furlong marker, matched strides with MURPHYS TIGER to deep stretch but could not get by the determined winner and just missed for the win, while securing the place. HONEYMOONZ OVER broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, set fast fractions through the turn, extended the lead into upper stretch, was asked for more inside of the furlong marker, could not hold off the top pair in deep stretch and held for show in the final stages. RACE.FOOTNOTES: REFI NOW forwardly placed in the early stages, raced on a snug hold while tracking the quick pace to the turn, came two wide to the quarter marker, ran in pursuit of FAST PER SE to mid-stretch, overtook that rival nearing the sixteenth-marker and kicked clear in deep stretch. FAST PER SE was sent to the early lead, showed good speed while carving out quick fractions to the quarter marker, held foes at bay to mid-stretch, was overtaken by REFI NOW nearing the sixteenth-marker, drifted in a bit in deep stretch, crowded MCGEORGE and just held for the place. MCGEORGE rated off of the fast early pace, saved ground to the quarter marker, came in a bit tight entering the stretch, rallied along the rail nearing the furlong pole, could not keep pace with REFI NOW in deep stretch, steadied in tight quarters inside of the sixteenth-marker and missed for the place, while holding for the show. THUNDER OF ZION shuffled back at the start and was off slowly, recovered to chase the fast early pace to the turn, raced two wide between rivals into the turn, was boxed in nearing the quarter marker, swung six wide for the drive and offered mild late rally. AMANOFMYSTATURE chased the fast early pace, raced three wide between runners into the turn, lost ground in upper stretch and lacked a late rally. PLAYING HARDBALL broke alertly then took back off of the fast early pace, mounted a four wide bid on the turn, could not sustain that run in the stretch and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: KODIACTION was allowed to settle in the early stages, raced two wide between runners into the far turn, came three wide to the quarter marker, was roused in upper stretch, closed with a rush inside of the furlong marker, came within aim in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to prevail in a blanket finish. TRIBAL NATION contested the pace leaving the break then ceded the early lead to STONE'S RIVER, tracked that rival through solid early fractions, made a steady gain on the pacesetter into the far turn, vied for the lead with STONE'S RIVER to mid-stretch, took a narrow lead inside of the furlong pole, dueled with STONE'S RIVER to deep stretch, felt late pressure from KODIACTION and was nailed on the line for the win, while earning the nod for the place. STONE'S RIVER away in good order and dictated terms into the first turn, set solid fractions while well handled through the backstretch run, was confronted by TRIBAL NATION nearing the quarter marker, battled with that foe to mid-stretch, lost the lead to TRIBAL NATION inside of the furlong pole, came again in deep stretch, was confronted by KODIACTION in the final strides and was gamely bested on the wire. SUNNY SPOT stalked the decent early fractions, maintained position through the backstretch run, was well placed into the far turn, raced two wide to the quarter marker, lost ground in upper stretch, closed willingly in the late stages but could not reel in the leaders in deep stretch. RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 1M All Weather Track CR: 91. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. (If a Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive a $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOTTERY PICK broke in and bumped with NATIONAL GENERAUX (IRE) at the start, still got good position going into the clubhouse turn, elected to track the leaders well in hand, started a bid with three-eighths to run, came into the stretch three wide, veered out and steadied slightly to avoid contact with SAREEHA (IRE) just past the eighth pole then found another gear and ran that one down in the shadow of the wire. SAREEHA (IRE) was away alertly, settled into a tracking position well behind the lone pacesetter, was always traveling well, set down for the lead approaching the quarter pole, was joined on the outside by LOTTERY PICK, held a clear lead mid-stretch then veered out under left handed urging, straightened out and got caught in the final yards. NICKEL NICKEL NINE bided time racing in mid-pack and towards the inside through the first half mile, kept to the inside through the far turn, waited patiently for racing room, tipped out into the two path at the head of the stretch, then attempted to go around LOTTERY PICK but had to alter course when that one veered out to avoid contact with another horse, then finished up well in the final sixteenth to gain third. NATIONAL GENERAUX (IRE) lunged out and bumped with LOTTERY PICK at the start, steadied slightly then trailed far behind for the first half mile, made a sweeping move around the turn to get into contention, came four wide into the stretch and continued to run on well to the finish. HEZA VALENTINE unhurried at the back of the field to the far turn, took a wide path around the turn while gaining some ground on the pack, angled towards the inside at the top of the stretch but could not sustain the bid and finished even-paced. BLUE SILVER sent from the break and was first into the turn, opened up on the field down the backstretch setting moderate fractions while well away from the rail, was challenged at the quarter pole, unable to keep up down and faded. RACKATAPTAP raced inside and near the rear of the field to the half mile marker, made mid-race move while saving ground along the far turn but stalled with a furlong to run. UPSTART YANKEE went three wide into the first turn, raced mid-pack of the spread out field down the backstretch while still wide, made a mild bid from the three eighths pole while still wide around the far turn then was outrun in the late stages.
